# Phase Documentation & Naming Rule

CRITICAL REQUIREMENTS:

- Every new chat MUST start with a title strictly following this format: `Phase XX: short phase description`.
- At the end of every task or chat interaction, you MUST document the result, current system status, and any pending issues.
- Create or update a markdown file in the `phases/` directory corresponding to the current phase (e.g., `phases/phase_42_remediation.md`).
- The phase document MUST contain the following sections:
  - Executive Summary
  - Changes Made
  - Current System Status (Pass/Fail/Blocked)
  - Next Steps / Open Items
  - Suggestions on impovements or optimizations
- Never commit the `phases/` directory to version control.
